# CLAUDE.md — Project Configuration for AI Agents

This file configures how AI agents (Claude Code, Codex, Cursor, etc.)
behave when working with this project.

---

## Git Commit Rules

- Always use `smart-git-commit` 5-part format: CONTEXT / CHANGE / WHY / IMPACT / footers
- Type/scope conventions for THIS project:

  | Area | Scope | Commit Type |
  |------|-------|-------------|
  | [FILL IN] | [FILL IN] | [FILL IN] |
  | [FILL IN] | [FILL IN] | [FILL IN] |

- Test command: `[FILL IN: npm test / pytest / cargo test / go test ./...]`
- Ticket prefix: `[FILL IN: GH / JIRA / LINEAR]`

---

## Branch Rules

- `feature/<ticket>-<short-description>` — new features
- `fix/<ticket>-<short-description>` — bug fixes
- `hotfix/<description>` — urgent production fixes
- `release/vX.Y.Z` — release preparation
- Never commit directly to: `main`, `master`, `develop`

---

## PR Rules

- Always create as draft first
- Must link to an issue or ticket
- Must pass all tests
- Must have no secrets in diff (run `bash scripts/scan-secrets.sh`)
- Title must match the most significant commit subject

---

## Release Rules

- Follow semver strictly: MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH
- Run `bash scripts/generate-changelog.sh` before tagging
- Always tag releases, never just push a version bump commit
- Pre-release tags: `vX.Y.Z-alpha.N`, `vX.Y.Z-beta.N`, `vX.Y.Z-rc.N`

---

## Quick Reference

```bash
# Security scan
bash scripts/scan-secrets.sh

# Run tests
bash scripts/detect-test-runner.sh

# Split mixed changesets
bash scripts/split-commits.sh

# Generate changelog
bash scripts/generate-changelog.sh

# Create PR
bash scripts/create-pr.sh

# Set git commit template
git config commit.template skills/smart-git-commit/templates/.gitmessage
```
